reviews: We had a wonderful stay at Hotel Maxim Folies. The staff when over and above to make our stay special which was greatly appreciated. The location of the hotel was excellent and within easy walking distance to the nearest metro station. The room was clean and had everything we needed for our stay. The staff were helpful and friendly and provided us with everything we needed. We will definitely stay again on our next trip to Paris!

Basic rooms are very small.
Beds are too short for tall persons.
Rooms facing the street are noisy. Better windows would help.
Hotel is at good location, nice lively district, metro is close.
Hotel and rooms are very clean.

The staff were lovely the location was great we had really nice meals in walking distance from the hotel each evening. The room was very clean and pretty it was a little small I do yoga daily and there was very little room but that was expected in Paris and the hotel reviews already let me know that the rooms were small but well designed and they are. I would definitely return to the hotel without hesitation. The hotel offers free coffee,water and pastries which is a lovely touch.

Very friendly staff. We always felt very welcome. Rooms small but big enough, also clean. Good breakfast. Some metro stations nearby, also some good restaurants, so I would say the location was perfect for us. We would come again.

Nice looking hotel. Rooms small, sink in main part of room, not in shower room m.

The problem was the toilet. The metal unit above the toilet that one uses to flush fell off which I was on the toilet ... I told reception as I was going out, but later happened again after my return. Short flush only, king one didn't work. Meanwhile, the toilet paper holder similarly deconstructed itself whilst in use.

Hot - well, warm-ish - water took a long time to heat up in the shower.

On the plus side, they use L'Occitaine soaps etc, and the scrambled egg at breakfast (with chives) was very good indeed. And guests can get coffee in the breakfast area during the day for free.

I felt welcomed at Maxim Folies. The room, although small-ish, was very comfortable (bed, good temperature, no noise) and clean. The towels were great. The breakfast had good choice and very good quality. Would stay again.

We thoroughly enjoyed our problem-free stay - soft bed, good temp control in room, attentive and responsive stay, good room cleaning, lots of hot water, excellent breakfast with wide variety of food items, great level of cleanliness throughout

We had a very pleasant stay at Maxim Folies.
The hotel is in a very good location, about one minute from the Grands Boulevards metro and 5 minutes to Cadet Metro. It is located on a quiet side street, hence no noise from the street. The hotel is well maintained.
All the staff we had dealings with were very pleasant, especially the young man at the reception. We managed to check in a bit early and while the final preparations to our room were being made, he prepared us a cup of coffee while we were waiting at the reception. I understood that the coffee machine at the reception was for the guests to use whenever they wanted.
We had a friend who was joining us for breakfast while we were there. That was also handled professionally, efficiently and pleasantly by the young gentleman at the reception. Our guest paid 15 euros for the breakfast before joining us and that was it, no further ado. We all agreed that the breakfast was of high quality, the selection of items was good and of high quality. It was regularly replenished and the service of the personnel in the breakfast was pleasant.
The room was small but cleverly designed. The toiletries in the bathroom were by L'occitane En Provence.
Also the checkout was pleasant and efficient. The young gentleman at the reception gave me precise instructions on how to find the closest ATM / bank.
A good stay and we would happily stay there again.

Great stay at the Maxim Folies. We loved the location which was walking distance to many sites and the metro to go further afield. The hotel felt very modern and the communal areas clean and presentable. The staff were really lovely and helpful and we couldn’t fault the service. The rooms were a good size, even for the smallest room we stayed in despite taking 3 suitcases, which is a bonus. The decor was nice, it felt very modern but with a Parisian edge, areas of the room could do with a slight touch up on paint etc. but to be expected in a city where short breaks are common and a high turn around of visitors. The hotel is a 15 minute walk from Gare du Nord so great for trains/Eurostar and felt quick and seamless from getting off to being checked in! Would recommend to friends and family travelling to Paris.

Only staying for one night so wanted somewhere reasonably priced and located, the Maxim Folies tick both those boxes. 15 minute walk from the Gare Du Nord and situated right be the Folies Bergere.
About a 15 minute walk to the Louvre and a few minutes from a a metro station. Lovely, friendly staff, they happily kept our luggage safe while we walked the city. Rooms are a reasonable side, nicely decorated and L'Occatane bathroom products! Decided to have the buffet breakfast for €15 person. Excellent coffee (even from a machine!) lots of pastries, pancakes, meats and cheeses to choose from. Well worth it, such a lovely relaxed atmosphere. Would definitely come again!!

The room was very clean and well-decorated, and despite being quite small it was excellent for our short stay in Paris. We were in Paris in a heat wave and the air-con in the room was working perfectly, for me this is very important, especially in the summer. The location is also excellent, close to Gare du Nord and Grand Boulevard. The breakfast was great and the staff was friendly and kind.

The hotel is in great location - with easy access to metro and bus. There are nice bars and restaurants in the area. The rooms are very well designed - they’re small, but efficient. It’s super clean and cosy. We totally enjoyed each time we returned to the room after a day in the city.

Cute boutique hotel. Conveniently located (across from the famous Follies Begere!). Decent room size (by European standards). Great shower and water pressure, cute chic lobby, decent complimentary breakfast offerings included in room price. Walking distance to Paris Opera House, Galleries Lafayette, Parfum Museum (all approx 10-15 mins).

Would stay again at Maxim Follies for sure.

We really loved our stay at Maxim Folies.
Cleanliness, courtesy and a very good breakfast.
A special mention to Fad at the reception: he is so kind and professional. He made us feel welcome in a very professional way.
If I had to mention a suggestion it would be to consider having an English speaking person during breakfast time. It happened to us a few times that the person who asked for room number could only speak French.

We enjoyed everything about this Hotel. Maxim Folies is located perfectly within 20 minutes walking to the opera or Galleries Lafayette. Two metrostations within 8 min walk. All the facilities are top in the hotel. It is very clean and the Hotel employess are very helpful and nice! We got engaged the second day we got in Paris, so we told the reception. A minute later we got a surprise at our hotelroom with a personal note, which made it an extra for us.

The breakfast is good and you can sit in a room with very nice interior. We enjoyed our stay there and will definetly be back when we will return to paris. Plus points are the location, the staff and the comfort.

We stayed at Hotel Maxim Folies for one night - timed with the Eurostar for two full days in Paris.

The hotel is perfectly located for those arriving into Gare de Nord - a 15 minute walk away. Check-in was very friendly and efficient with the wonderful Jill who made us feel incredibly welcome despite our short stay. Our luggage was stored before check-in at 3pm and after check-out on our last day - meaning most of our time in the city was without baggage.

We booked a Superior Room which, while very small, had everything a couple would need for one or two nights away. The bathroom was incredibly well appointed and the bed was very comfortable.

The room had total blackout curtains and looked out onto a communal courtyard. We didn’t eat breakfast at the hotel - though this was offered for €15pp, there were cheaper and more attractive options within a minute’s walk.

Overall, we’ll definitely be back at Hotel Maxim Folies.

The location is very good, just off the Rue Lafayette from Gare du Nord (Eurostar terminal) Fairly quiet, nice staff, really good breakfast with quality meats etc.
The room was spotless, it is a little small, but you expect that in the centre of a large city. Kettle available, TV, heating and air con. Comfy bed, good bedding, good shower. Would definitely go back.

We booked here as we like the Opera area as a base for going to the 6 nations games. It was our first time in Maxim Foiles and it did not disappoint. We booked the suites and while small they were perfect for the weekend. They gave us extra space and didn’t feel on top of each other.
The hotel is spotlessly clean, lovely L’occetaine toiletries, staff are so friendly and helpful (special mention to Jill who was so helpful with our booking). Breakfast was lovely, just right to start the day.
We walked everywhere as it’s a good location, we did the TootToot bus tour as a quick way to see the main sights.
Highly recommend Maxim Foiles will stay here again if we return to Paris

Situated among many independent small restaurants and bars, it is a lovely place to come back to after visiting the sights. A boutique hotel, with stylish decor, super clean, with staff who were so keen to help with anything required, and were friendly and professional in just the right measure. The 2 adjacent rooms suited our family perfectly. We hope to go back again, our 1 night stay just wasn’t long enough!

Good hotel, in relation to the price quality. At the reception are all attentive and friendly, all well organized. Shampo and L'occitane shower gel which I liked very much, by default hotels have cheap products. In the room there was nespresso coffee machine, fantastic. The clothes in the room were changed every day. The only problem I found was the amount of dust in the air. It really burned my eyes to the point where they went red. It's the only weakness. So the experience was very good and I'll be back.

I went to Paris for a quick three day city break. I stayed at this hotel and the staff were lovely. The bed was very comfortable and the bathroom was very aesthetically pleasing. The room had a balcony and it perfected the Parisian experience. Highly recommend for a lovely, affordable yet rich experience.

We arrived early evening for a 3 night stay. Check in was quick, reception staff were friendly, helpful and efficient. There was a lift. Complimentary tea, coffee and soft drinks were available in the breakfast area at any time. Our room was small but perfectly formed. It was spotlessly clean. There was a great shower and air conditioning. Decor is modern and a little quirky. Lots of places to eat nearby and the hotel is a short walk to Cadet metro stop.

Amazing.

Nice staff !

Amazing food!

Great ambiance!

WILL COME BACK !!!!!

Much better than other places we stayed on our trip!

Location is phenomenal also!!

I don’t want to say more because if it gets too popular then it might lose its touch!!!

I stayed 2 nts with my wife.
Everything is perfect.(Location, Room; breakfast, Staff)
Price quality ratio %100.
I advise honestly to everybody who plan to visit Paris whrther for leisure or Busines.
Thanks for everything

We took a suite here recently for 3 of us (ladies) for a night in Paris. Felt entirely safe with the location and the room. Totally clean, cool decor, nice shower, good toiletries, good breakfast, and lovely service. The food out couch was a bit on the hard side, but after a few wines in Paris - who cares! Easy walking distance to the Louvre etc, and a great area to explore. Plenty of supermarkets, bars and restaurants nearby. 15 minute easy walk from the Gare du Nord - really great location.

Pleasant and friendly staff. Central location with many restaurants and shops nearby. Near metro and within walking distance to the lourve and galleri la fayette. Would stay here Again. Many thanks to the front desk who were so friendly and helpful.

We stayed at maxim folies for 2nights. Friendly staff, clean rooms but a bit dark and a bit noisy probably because our room is at first floor. A lot of restaurants nearby and you can just walk to shopping areas. Taxi is very accessible too. A great experience at this hotel wiah we could stay longer.

Hotel Maxim Folies is perfectly positioned in the vibrant 9th arrondissement. We selected this hotel for its central location including three metro lines all within a short walking distance from the hotel that allowed quick access to sightseeing hotspots. The hotel was also positioned among an excellent range of dining options, ‘happy hour’ bars, supermarkets plus there was a laundromat conveniently across the road.

All staff we interacted with during our stay were wonderfully friendly, helpful and spoke English to assist with check-in/out, general directions and questions. Merci!

The hotel and rooms have been renovated with a stylish yet vibrant vibe. Our room was compact but comfortable with a comfy bed, hot shower, storage space including a safe and heating/cooling - everything you need from a hotel room. The complimentary L’Occitane products were a nice touch.

Just renovated but not defigured. Personnel well prepared and very kind. Good wi-fi connection, cleanliness, mattress, and decoration. A great touch: a Nespresso machine in the room and another in the reception - free capsules. Even with the Euro so expensive, this hotel is a bargain. My first choice next time.

This hotel is conveniently located for those arriving at Gare du Nord. You can walk to the hotel in approx 15 minutes. Or there are 3 Metro stations all within 5 minutes of the hotel, taking you to most corners of Paris.

The hotel itself has been recently refurbished. The room we had was small, but typical of a capital city hotel, we expected this and it was not a problem. The furniture and fixing in the room were nice, the bed was comfy. Of note was the exposed brass fittings in the bathroom. To improve it would have been nice to have somewhere to dry the towels.

Though the hotel had been refurbished for some reason the lift was missed out. It was shabby and the light and control panel were held together with tape. This gave the wrong impression to the hotel. This poor first impression as we went to our room for the first time detracts from an otherwise lovely and quirky decorated hotel that was clean and tidy.

The breakfast was disappointing. Cutlery and crockery were hard to find if you came down for a slightly later breakfast (0830), not the best selection of food, and the coffee machine did the worst coffee we had in Paris during this trip.

That, being said, it deserves my 4 star rating for the good service on reception, the decor and the location, it could be 5 with a little more effort with the breakfast.

I just love this place.
Great location, good breakfast, awesome staff.
Cozy and super clean rooms. The wifi works just perfect. Definitely I will choose this
hotel in a future. You are close of the main attractions and the closest metro station is just 3 blocks away.

Lovely reception desk staff. Decent option for breakfast. Very well located in a great neighborhood. Lots of restaurants, bars, shops, cafes nearby. Rooms are pleasant, if smallish (but that's most of Paris for you).

We have just returned from a 2 night stay at this hotel and WOW, what an amazing choice.

It is situated in a perfect location close to the metro. Upon arrival, the reception staff were so friendly and welcoming.

We were in room 602 and it was spotless. Yes they are small but so what! They are immaculately clean and the comfiest beds weve ever stayed in. Complementary shower gels and toiletries in the room too.

Theres a beautiful restaurant literally next door where we ate. Reasonable prices and fantastic service.

We paid €14 each for breakfast in the hotel and it was worth every penny.

I cannot speak highly enough of this hotel. The staff go out of their way to make your stay comfortable. When we return to Paris we will definitely be staying here.

Thanks to everyone at Maxim Follies!

Stayed for 2 night with my husband.

The hotel is in a fab location, near to several metro stations and surrounded by bars and restaurants.

The room was small but we only slept and got ready in it. We found the room clean and the beds very comfy with lovely pillows. The shower is amazing also.

The staff were so friendly and even let us check in early. On our last day we were not leaving until the evening, they kept our luggage safe for the day while we went out.

I would definitely recommend.

We stayed at the Maxim Folies for 4 days...our stay was very pleasant and the staff were very helpful. One of the best things for me was the less than 10 min walk to the Metro and the free coffee in the lobby. You can even take it to go.

At first, seeing the size of the room, with the sink out by the door, I was taken aback... but it has it's advantages. One of us could use the sink while the other was using the bathroom. So be prepared for that.
The breakfast spread was a bit limited for us vegetarians, but what they lacked in variety they made up in quantity. The croissants and muffins were yummy and we had our fill of them, apart from fresh fruits and juices. In the evenings you can sit by the window and have some wine, watching the world go by, which we did on a rainy evening. They have very limited service when it comes to food, but there are plenty of very good restaurants close by.

It was value for money, with good service, centrally located. I have to mention the very nice staff again. They really made our stay in Paris very comfortable.

My sister and I stayed at this hotel for 2 nights. Firstly I must commend the staff that work here. They were very helpful and accommodating from booking all the way to check out. The hotel is located is a nice spot in Paris with a metro stop (cadet) less then 5 mins walk away.
The room was lovely, loved the decor. It’s small but as it was a city break was all we needed. The bed was very comfortable.
The only reason I didn’t give this hotel a 5 was because of the noise. Now when I say the noise it didn’t really bother us but may bother some people who are light sleepers. You can hear the floorboards in the hall creak, people next door taking close off the rail and chargers out of the wall. There was also building work opposite us which started at 8am. But as I mentioned before this didn’t really disrupt us too much and would definitely recommend the hotel.

We had a nice stay at Maxim Folies with the family. Everything is fine and it went smoothly. The rooms are good but be aware of most of Paris hotel has small rooms. This is nothing to blame the hotel for. Some of our wall sockets didn't work and this is something that can happen to everyone, but the negative side of this is the reception told we used fake chargers even we used the original ones. I investigated the issue and it was the hotel lamp that triggered the fuse to go off. We didn't bother discuss it further and enjoyed Paris. Next thing is you can hear the swing in the lobby in the first floor rooms.
However very nice and kind reception overall.

we stayed here with my brother for 2 days. The first thing i would like to say is the location (Grand Boulevard) is the best place to stay in Paris. Hotel is very close to the metro stations (both Cadet and G. Boulevard) and the city . Ladies at the reception were very very helpful and always polite. only negative issue i need to write was the smell in the room. could not understand where was it coming from but did not worried about it a lot because we were only sleeping in the room. So it was ok..Do not hesitate to stay at this hotel!
